def: The service or sacrifice of the Mass.
One who, or that which, dubs.
To construct wrongly; to construe or interpret erroneously.
A wild Irish plunderer, esp. one of the 17th century; -- socalled from his carrying a half-pike, called a rapary. [Written alsoraparee.]
The moor cock, or red grouse. See Grouse. [Prov. Eng.]
Be it as it may; nevertheless; notwithstanding; although;albeit; yet; but; however.The Moor -- howbeit that I endure him not -Is of a constant, loving,noble nature. Shak.
One who, or that which, devastates. Emerson.
Boiling up or over; hence, manifesting exhilaration orexcitement, as of feeling; effervescing. "Ebullient with subtlety."De Quincey.The ebullient enthusiasm of the French. Carlyle.
Around the viscera; as, the perivisceral cavity.
